# FleetCart: new module / feature checklist

When adding a **new module**, **admin feature**, or **significant function**, complete all items before considering the work done.

## Translations (all supported locales)

This project uses **English (`en`) and Bahasa Malaysia (`ms`)** at minimum.

1. Add strings to `modules/{Module}/Resources/lang/en/*.php` — never hardcode UI copy in Blade/JS.
2. Mirror keys in `modules/{Module}/Resources/lang/ms/*.php` with proper BM (not English leftovers).
3. Use `trans('module::file.key')` in views, tabs, validation `availableAttributes`, and flash messages.
4. After lang changes: run `php artisan translation:refresh-cache --sync` (all modules) or `php artisan loyalty:sync-translations` (Loyalty only). Also `php artisan view:clear` if Blade still shows keys.
5. Optional helper: `php scripts/sync-ms-translations.php` to seed missing `ms` keys from `en`.
6. **Loyalty module:** run `php artisan loyalty:sync-translations` after adding keys (syncs en/ms to DB + refreshes loader cache). In Blade, use `LoyaltyLang::get('tiers.form.key')` when keys may be missing from stale cache.

## Admin role permissions

Every admin route/action must be gated and assignable in **Roles → Permissions** and **Users → Permissions**.

1. Define `modules/{Module}/Config/permissions.php` (groups → actions → `module::permissions.*` keys).
2. Add labels in `Resources/lang/en/permissions.php` and `Resources/lang/ms/permissions.php`.
3. Protect routes/controllers with `hasAccess('admin.module.action')` (or project middleware equivalent).
4. Grant default access to admin roles via seeder/command if needed (see `Loyalty` grant-permissions command pattern).
5. If a **custom** `UserController` (or similar) overrides `update`/`store`, **must** persist `permissions` from the request (use `Permission::prepare` via `$user->permissions = $request->input('permissions', [])` — do not only `except(['permissions'])`).

## UI copy conventions

- Admin locale MS: sentence case labels; avoid `text-transform: uppercase` on BM labels unless intentional.
- Permission radios: default **Inherit** checked so all keys submit with the form.

## Quick self-check before PR

- [ ] `en` + `ms` keys exist for every new user-facing string
- [ ] `Config/permissions.php` + lang permission labels added
- [ ] Routes guarded; role/user permission UI shows new module
- [ ] User/role save paths persist permissions when applicable
